    "information_content_info_UPQR94": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_JLGwxY": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Aries (21st March - 19th April)",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Aries (21st March - 19th April)",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "aries",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_eWhYET": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Ruled by Mars, the planet associated with energy and action, and represented by the Ram, Aries is the first sign of the zodiac. As the first sign of an astrological element, Aries falls into 'fire,' and Aries tends to be fiery, bold, energetic, and tending to lead in a new direction. Aries individuals are natural-born leaders and are willing to jump in and lead. Their courageous instincts encourage them to take on challenges and take them on without thinking twice. They tend to fall prey to their impulsivity, leading them to act spontaneously without thinking about the consequences. Aries value their independence and usually experience their greatest satisfaction when they can control their own experience. Their zest and strong drive move others to act and break through their own barriers. At their best, Aries are courageous, adventurous, and fiercely loyal. Aries may benefit from managing impulsivity with a little patience and thought.</p><ul><li>A rose-gold gemstone ring with shimmering diamonds will complement Aries' courageous and passionate personality traits. </li></ul>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_JLGwxY",
        "richtext_eWhYET"
      ],
      "name": "Aries (21st March - 19th April)",
      "settings": {
        "full_width": false,
        "show_on_homepage": false
      }
    },
    "information_content_info_7GPqfR": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_hK9JaP": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Taurus (20th April - 20th May)",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Taurus (20th April - 20th May)",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "taurus",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_DAXEXx": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Taurus, the second sign of the zodiac, is ruled by Venus, the planet of love and beauty, and is represented by the Bull. An earth sign, Taurus is stable, dependable, and patient. Taurus Individuals have strong appreciation for the pleasures of a good life: food, comfort, and beauty. Taurus pursues life-assured, taking their time - a methodical approach to fulfilling the goals they set. Taurus likes to feel safe, enjoying stability in their relationships and finances. Taurus is loyal and devoted, but stubbornness has a negative side: changing routine is not easy. A Taurus at its finest is hardworking, practical, and nurturing-Supporting their people intentionally and faithfully. A flexible, open attitude might help avoid falling into old habits.</p><ul><li>Taurus pendants, gemstone earrings, or stylish stone jewelry in yellow gold featuring emeralds goes a long way to complement Taurus’ strong and caring nature. </li></ul>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_hK9JaP",
        "richtext_DAXEXx"
      ],
      "name": "Taurus (20th April - 20th May)",
      "settings": {
        "full_width": false,
        "show_on_homepage": false
      }
    },
    "information_content_info_JAbpDR": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_k9RJ9N": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Gemini (21st May - 20th June)",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Gemini (21st May - 20th June)",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "gemini",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_MewpkK": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>The third sign of the zodiac, Gemini, is ruled by the planet of communication and intellect, Mercury, and is represented by Twins. Gemini, a sign of the air, is curious, adaptable, and mentally quick. Gemini individuals enjoy juggling multiple interests while seeking fun, new experiences, and continuing to pursue knowledge. Their dual nature allows a differing viewpoint, but can be a detriment in the way they are perceived as inconsistent or wishy-washy. The agile nature of Gemini typically plays well in social settings. They have a charm, wittiness, and mindset that serve well in conversation. They enjoy a stimulating atmosphere that uses their intellectual curiosity and enjoy conversation or debate. The best side of Gemini is when they show a versatile, communicative, and imaginative side that is full of new ideas or the ability to adapt. They may also benefit from focusing on one thing at a time or slowing down to not feel scattered.</p><ul><li>Elegant earrings, necklaces, and bold rings featuring white gold and pearls will improve your focus and communication skills. </li></ul>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_k9RJ9N",
        "richtext_MewpkK"
      ],
      "name": "Gemini (21st May - 20th June)",
      "settings": {
        "full_width": false,
        "show_on_homepage": false
      }
    },
    "information_content_info_PJ4VGq": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_JYeqWV": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Cancer (21st June - 22nd July)",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Cancer (21st June - 22nd July)",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "cancer",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_63rWC4": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Cancer, the number four sign in the zodiac, is ruled by the Moon, symbolism for feelings and intuition, which is represented in its symbol, the Crab. Emotional, nurturing, and protective are all aspects of water signs, including Cancer. Cancers tend to know their own feelings and the feelings of others, lending them a sense of empathy and caring that is often recognised in a Cancer. Generally, Cancers are very intuitive, with the ability to form close emotional bonds with those they care about. They place the highest priority on home and family because they wish to be protected and comfortable in a safe environment. Their sensitivity can lead them to be caring, yet it can raise their insecurity and moodiness In the best of circumstances, Cancers can be loving, loyal, and intuitive drivers of security and comfort for others. Cancers could benefit from setting days on either side of them and avoiding withdrawal when they feel trapped.</p><ul><li>Astrology necklaces, astrology pendants, or zodiac sign pendants in white gold featuring rubies balance lunar energy and boost calm emotions and intuition. </li></ul>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_JYeqWV",
        "richtext_63rWC4"
      ],
      "name": "Cancer (21st June - 22nd July)",
      "settings": {
        "full_width": false,
