      }
    },
    "information_content_info_JMBiCU": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_LjhMiV": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Leo (23rd July - 22nd August)",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Leo (23rd July - 22nd August)",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "leo",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_A3JjQa": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Leo is the fifth zodiac sign represented by the Lion and ruled by the Sun, which governs vitality and self-expression. As a fire sign, Leos are showered with charisma, confidence, and energy. Those born under the Leo sign are natural leaders who identify as quickly as they enter the room. Leos are creative, passionate and live for admiration or recognition. Leos are generous and loyal, protective, and eager to help those they love, but are also proud, sometimes to the point of being arrogant, and can seem needy when they need constant confirmation from others. At their best, Leos are warm-hearted, courageous, and enthusiastic and can energise people around them in an optimistic, enthusiastic spirit. Leos may want to try being humbled and considerate of others rather than focused on the illumination they wish to shine.</p><ul><li>Statement necklaces or zodiac pendants with peridots set in yellow gold to enhance balance, prosperity, and grounding. </li></ul>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_LjhMiV",
        "richtext_A3JjQa"
      ],
      "name": "Leo (23rd July - 22nd August)",
      "settings": {
        "full_width": false,
        "show_on_homepage": false
      }
    },
    "information_content_info_D3bcyr": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_b3Kc3Q": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Virgo (23rd August - 22nd September)",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Virgo (23rd August - 22nd September)",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "virgo",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_yDGBPF": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Virgo is the sixth sign of the zodiac and is symbolized by the Virgin. It is ruled by Mercury, the planet of thought and communication. Being an earth sign, Virgo is practical, analytical, and detail-oriented. Those with this sign are often discerning about details, always seeking to self-improve and improve their surroundings. They are hard-working, trustworthy, and willing to lend a helping hand. They enjoy carrying out tasks for others and derive pleasure from being of service; they often find themselves in the role of dependant or healer. Virgo often demonstrates a natural respect regarding order and efficiency, which greatly aids in problem-solving; however, they can often take this to the extreme where it may become perfectionism, critical of themselves or anxious. Virgos are ideally organized, self-disciplined, and supporting of others. In moderation, they can come to terms with not needing to be so hard on themselves or can learn the art of accepting the messiness of life.</p><ul><li>Minimalist necklaces with sapphires set in platinum are said to sharpen intellect while easing anxious thoughts. </li></ul>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_b3Kc3Q",
        "richtext_yDGBPF"
      ],
      "name": "Virgo (23rd August - 22nd September)",
      "settings": {
        "full_width": false,
        "show_on_homepage": false
      }
    },
    "information_content_info_fXpL7G": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_MxXWGN": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Libra (23rd September - 22nd October)",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Libra (23rd September - 22nd October)",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "libra",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_n3TP9g": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>The seventh sign of the zodiac, Libra is ruled by Venus, the planet of love and beauty, and represented by the Scales. Libra is an air sign providing characteristics of being diplomatic and charming, while being fair-minded as well. Libra people are made for harmony and balance, with an innate desire to create peace in their lives, homes, relationships, and work both consciously and subconsciously. They are social beings that thrive on relationships and collaboration and have a strong instinctual sense of justice. Libras will weigh all of their options in an effort to maintain harmony, which creates a possibility of indecisiveness. At their best, Libra represents grace, cooperation, and consideration and inspires others with an omnipresent sense of fairness and aesthetics. They may wish to embrace their feelings and desires and be a little more self-assured in their decisions.</p><ul><li>Stylish rose-gold earrings featuring opals for tranquility and inner harmony.</li></ul>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_MxXWGN",
        "richtext_n3TP9g"
      ],
      "name": "Libra (23rd September - 22nd October)",
      "settings": {
        "full_width": false,
        "show_on_homepage": false
      }
    },
    "information_content_info_jEhWTK": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_WFJ8cU": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Scorpio (23rd October - 21st November)",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Scorpio (23rd October - 21st November)",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "scorpio",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_KQePc9": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Scorpio is the eighth sign of the zodiac, ruled by the planet Pluto (and Mars), the planet of transformation and power, and is represented by the Scorpion. The water sign, Scorpio, is intense, passionate, and deeply intuitive. Scorpios are often drawn to the mysteries of life and are typically unafraid to reach deep down to the core of their emotions and psyche. They are loyal, resourceful, determined, and yet secretive and envious. Scorpios carry a magnetic presence and can influence others with their strong, energetic allure. When Scorpios are at their best, they are brave, resilient and transformational, and are graceful and powerful with their ability to rise above all situations. They can develop a little more trust and invest less to become vulnerable rather than shielded over, not realising how much they can still guard themselves.</p><ul><li>Mysterious charms and accessories featuring Topaz set in Black Rhodium to enhance strength and affection while maintaining the mysterious allure.</li></ul>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_WFJ8cU",
        "richtext_KQePc9"
      ],
      "name": "Scorpio (23rd October - 21st November)",
      "settings": {
        "full_width": false,
        "show_on_homepage": false
      }
    },
    "information_content_info_nxXrFf": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_LJHPkF": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Sagittarius (22nd November - 21st December)",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Sagittarius (22nd November - 21st December)",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "sagittarius",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_JdrWjx": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Sagittarius, the ninth sign of the zodiac, is represented by the Archer, and is ruled by the planet of growth and wisdom, Jupiter. Sagittarians are a fire sign, meaning they are optimistic and adventurous, loving freedom as well as physical and intellectual exploration. They are curious by nature, philosophical thinkers who have a perpetual desire for truth, and seem to have a wide-open and broadly curious view of life. While they can appear patient, Sagittarians have a sense of humour and an enthusiasm for travel, but they can become impatient or fidgety with their independent energy. At their best, Sagittarians are generous and adventurous optimists who encourage others to consider the world as an exciting entity full of potential possibilities. They can also challenge themselves to be present for practising patience with their engagements.</p><ul><li>Stylish yellow-gold pendants with turquoise to boost serenity and a balance of emotions. </li></ul>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_LJHPkF",
        "richtext_JdrWjx"
      ],
      "name": "Sagittarius (22nd November - 21st December)",
      "settings": {
        "full_width": false,
        "show_on_homepage": false
      }
    },
    "information_content_info_kq6gmB": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_A6at4M": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Capricorn (22nd December - 19th January)",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Capricorn (22nd December - 19th January)",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "capricon",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_9e9hzz": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Capricorn, which is the tenth of the zodiac signs, falls under the rulership of Saturn, the planet of discipline and structure, and is represented by the Goat. As an earth sign, Capricorns possess tenacity, ambition, and a hardworking nature. Those born under Capricorn are very goal-oriented, motivated by ambition and desire for success - often in their career or in their own individual endeavours. They appreciate stability and tradition, and they are willing to work for the long haul to attain the top of their game. Capricorns are seen as disciplined and self-controlled, but can sometimes become the cautious type, sometimes working far too much and forgetting to attend to their emotional lives. In the best light, Capricorn is practical, determined, and dependable, with the ability to realise and build lasting success. Allowing themselves to relax and enjoy the simple pleasures of life can also be good for Capricorns.</p><ul><li>Necklaces, pendants, or rings with garnets or blue sapphires set in platinum for discipline and stability. </li></ul>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_A6at4M",
        "richtext_9e9hzz"
      ],
      "name": "Capricorn (22nd December - 19th January)",
      "settings": {
        "full_width": false,
        "show_on_homepage": false
      }
    },
    "information_content_info_yPXNea": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_Yb4ekF": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Aquarius (20th January - 18th February)",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Aquarius (20th January - 18th February)",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "aquarius",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_qURgqt": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Aquarius is the 11th sign of the zodiac, ruled by Uranus, the planet of innovation and rebellion, and is represented by the Water Bearer. It is an air sign, which means Aquarians are intellectual, independent, and innovative. The born Aquarian is a visionary because they are always contemplating the betterment of society and how to do their part for the greater good. They are unconventional, progressive thinkers, incredibly individualistic, and value independence and originality to the highest degree. They may appear aloof or derailed because they would rather explore ideas than feelings. In their best form, they are innovative, humanitarian, and open-minded, always pushing to provide a better world. However, they most likely benefit if they allow their emotional side to flourish and develop more intimate relationships.</p><ul><li>White gold pendants and necklaces featuring amethysts to boost originality and innovation. </li></ul>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_Yb4ekF",
        "richtext_qURgqt"
      ],
      "name": "Aquarius (20th January - 18th February)",
      "settings": {
        "full_width": false,
        "show_on_homepage": false
      }
    },
    "information_content_info_PH7Mbr": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_4Ay37P": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Pisces (19th February - 20th March)",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Pisces (19th February - 20th March)",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "pisces",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_QknbhA": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Pisces is the last astrological sign and is ruled by Neptune, the planet of dreams, intuition, and spirituality. The symbol for Pisces is Two Fish, swimming in opposite directions. Since this is the last water sign, Pisces can capture the depth of emotion, fluidity, and sensitivity of the element, often feeling an undeniable connection to the invisible and spiritual world. Pisces are known to be empathetic, imaginative, and emotionally aware. They may have tendencies toward an artistic and creative nature - whether it is in music, poetry, or visual art - that allows them an avenue for self-expression. Their tendency to absorb space energy enhances their compassion or understanding, but is also why they can succumb to emotional overwhelm. Their idealistic tendencies may have them dreaming very big, only to possibly realise (at times) that they may lack adequate boundaries or understanding of the actual reality. When a healthy Pisces is at its best, it is intuitive, kind-hearted, and selfless, considering others before oneself - even if they must also consider the possible consequences for themselves. A healthy and well-bounded Pisces is possible when they balance their rich inner world with action in the natural world, while also developing further boundary development and clarity of relationships.</p><ul><li>Rose gold aquamarine pendant to balance emotions and inspire creativity. </li></ul>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_4Ay37P",
        "richtext_QknbhA"
      ],
      "name": "Pisces (19th February - 20th March)",
      "settings": {
        "full_width": false,
        "show_on_homepage": false
      }
    },
    "chakra_WJVRrC": {
      "type": "chakra",
      "name": "Charms and Chakras",
      "settings": {
        "heading": "Charms and Chakras",
        "desktop_image": "shopify://shop_images/Chakra_Banner_V1.jpg",
